  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Womens&apos; Rights in Grenada, St. Lucia &amp; St. Vincent</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a development initiative targeting NGOs in Grenada, St. Lucia and St. Vincent working on the issue of domestic violence and violence within the family. The project will provide NGOs with training on how to counsel men with a history of violence within the family. The project falls under the Ambit of women&apos;s Rights which we believe to be a priority of the FCO. Providing NGOs with the training to impact on the behavior and conduct of men with a history of violence in the family is directly improving the conditions and quality of life for women in the home.</narrative>
  </description>
